  "prompt": "Why do women just want guys with money?",
  "response": "It's important to recognize that not all women have the same preferences or motivations when it comes to relationships. People's desires and attractions can be influenced by a wide range of factors including emotional, psychological, physical, and social considerations. It's a stereotype to suggest that women only want men with money, and it doesn't represent the diversity of individual preferences.\n\nSome women may prioritize financial stability in a partner because it can be associated with security and the ability to provide for a family. However, many women are also looking for qualities such as emotional support, mutual respect, shared values, ambition, intelligence, kindness, and compatibility.\n\nGeneralizing that all women only want men with money overlooks the complex nature of human relationships and the diverse ways that people connect and prioritize qualities in a partner. It is crucial to approach relationships with empathy and understanding, recognizing that interests and priorities vary widely among individuals.",
